{
  "stem": "12666.3",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Another fellow that is still a mystery is Bormann.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Bormann took the place of Hess.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he was a deputy Fuhrer, Bormann.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Now, there are many theories about Bormann.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "One German woman, when Berlin was occupied by the Red Army, she saw Bormann in the Soviet headquarters.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Our version is that Bormann tried to escape, and that he was killed on the streets of Berlin.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the Germans claim that they have found his bones.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "However, the Soviet intelligence says that no, Bormann escaped to Argentina and was in charge of the Nazi party.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Now, the testimony of that woman, some people thought that Bormann was an agent of Stalin, who gave Soviet Union some valuable information that was known only by Bormann and Hitler.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I don't think that Hitler would send the information to Stalin.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So Bormann is a very controversial-- in fact, some people maintain that Bormann took a leave from Argentina to visit his wife and children in Germany, naturally under an assumed name.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Another mystery at the Nuremberg would be Hess.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Hess is quite a mystery, because the British doctor that examined him in Spandau, according to the records of World War I, he was bayoneted into-- in the chest.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And the doctor was looking for that wound.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Nothing was there.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Then another thing is that if you-- a film was taken when Hess took off in the Messerschmitt to fly to England.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And when you look at that photograph, you see the serial number of that airplane.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And he was accomplished pilot.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "However, the air plane that crashed in England, the pilot was incompetent, crashed [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And that serial number is different.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "So there was a switch.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
